8-05 01:06:37','<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7516,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Ignoring-online-marketing-is-like-opening-a-business-and-not-telling-a-soul_-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7516\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:atomic-blocks/ab-drop-cap {\"dropCapFontSize\":2} -->\n<div style=\"color:#32373c\" class=\"wp-block-atomic-blocks-ab-drop-cap drop-cap-letter ab-font-size-2 ab-block-drop-cap\"><div class=\"ab-drop-cap-text\"><p>The internet is such a big part of our lives now and it has completely changed the way in which we bank, shop, consume media and socialise. </p></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:atomic-blocks/ab-drop-cap -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Newspaper and magazine have become mostly <a href=\"https://www.crikey.com.au/2020/05/04/australia-magazines-disruption-bauer/\">defunct</a> in Australia, as readership has dwindled and advertising costs have remained high; needless to say this means advertisers have been paying the same advertising rates for a lesser result.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>TV advertising has also taken a <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/digital-ad-spend-to-overtake-tv-in-2017-studies-find\">hit</a>; once considered the gold standard of effective advertising in Australia, ad free streaming services such as Netflix and Stan have drawn audiences away from mainstream TV. Audiences for years were frustrated with the increasing amount of ads on TV, but they tolerated it when no other options were available. Streaming services have provided a solution to this problem, thus creating a mass exodus from commercial TV. This applies to the embattled <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/news-corp-s-billion-dollar-write-down-for-foxtel#:~:text=News%20Corp%20has%20written%20down,nearly%20%24US1%20billion%20(AUD1.&amp;text=27%20billion%20(AUD3.,of%20%24US1%20billion%20(AUD1.\">Foxte</a>l as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These events mean Australian businesses are spending more money than ever on digital marketing: in 2017 we spent 3.43 billion advertising online, and in 2019 we spent a whopping <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/australian-brands-spent-9-4-billion-on-digital-ads-in-2019\">9.4 billion</a>, which is significantly higher than the previous forecast of 4.97 billion for <a href=\"https://www.adnews.com.au/news/digital-ad-spend-to-overtake-tv-in-2017-studies-find\">2019</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Aside from the obvious fact that digital marketing is now more effective than traditional media, it also offers a degree of transparency. You no longer have to place an ad and cross your fingers it works for you, all of the data is readily available through the many digital analytics platforms so you know exactly how each dollar translates into web traffic, social media traffic, engagement and sales. I use <a href=\"https://databox.com/\">databox</a> to track all of these metrics with clients. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is one caveat to my previous statement though: although transparency and data are a surety in the digital age, none of those metrics are guaranteed to translate into sales for your business. This presents a problem to the everyday business owner who is running their own digital campaigns. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is a sense of achievement and the feeling of being in control; you\'re spending money and you can see its resulting in extra likes to your page, more followers, more traffic, more page views. There is really only one question to ask yourself  at this point:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote {\"className\":\"is-style-large\"} -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-style-large\"><p>\"Are your current digital marketing efforts translating into sales?</p><p></p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the answer is yes, then awesome keep doing what you\'re doing if you\'re happy with your figures. If the answer is no, then it\'s really time to engage with a professional to maximise the results you\'re getting for your ad spend. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My goal when conducting digital campaigns for clients, at the very least is to cover my cost. That is the money you as the client spends on hiring me to manage your marketing is offset by the increase in results you attain from hiring a professional. This effect is also compounded by the fact that you now have a lot more time that you were spending on marketing, to other facets of your business. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:block {\"ref\":7586} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Google analytics gives us the data for your web traffic, organic search, paid search, keyword ranking, click through traffic from social and external URL\'s. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Google Analytics</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":7600,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/morning-brew-NrOUHQ2jHtU-unsplash-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7600\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->','Digital Marketing','','inherit','closed','closed','','7436-revision-v1','','','2020-08-05 01:06:37','2020-08-05 01:06:37','',7436,'https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/7436-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(7599,1,'2020-08-05 01:02:59','2020-08-05 01:02:59','<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7519,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Ignoring-online-marketing-is-like-opening-a-business-and-not-telling-a-soul_-1-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7519\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">When you visit a website that just has a basic service offering and a phone number what\'s your honest first impression? Do they seem trustworthy to you? Or at the very least, does anything on that site motivate you to take action in any way? The answer is most likely no. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Let me paint you a picture. Your cupboard falls off its hinge. You bought a new joiner and it kept coming out. You\'ve tried to fix it to no avail. So you google how to fix a cupboard join, and you find a helpful blog post from a local carpenter on how to fix the exact issue you\'re having. Except you\'re not a carpenter and your cupboard is still broken. Who are you going to call to fix it? The local carpenter with the helpful blog post who has gone out of his way to help you for free, or another carpenter who\'s website sits contentless? Who has built more trust and authority with you, the business with valuable content or the one with nothing? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote {\"className\":\"is-style-large\"} -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-style-large\"><p>The best way to build authority is to create high quality, educational content and continuing to do it over time. </p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">This is where the saying content is king comes from. Content is the defining difference between action and hesitation, or more bluntly between gaining and losing a sale. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">You should offer the best possible content, for free. Good content is relevant to your audience, helpful to solve their problems and well researched. And when I say relevant that means don\'t post cat videos or personal photos to your social media channels when you\'re trying to build credibility. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">You\'ll know you\'re crushing your content marketing goals when you are getting an increase in engagement on social, and increase in traffic to your website and an increase in people contacting you wanting to work together. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">I will be posting more about this topic and content marketing methods in detail, but service available include: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":7565,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/green-chameleon-s9CC2SKySJM-unsplash-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7565\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Content Writing</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Content writing for your website, blog, press releases and social media articles. All content is researched and proof read for you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Explainer Videos</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Explainer or promotional videos for your website, online course or social media channels. All videos 