 href=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/digitalmarketing/\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/austin-distel-tLZhFRLj6nY-unsplash-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"Facebook advertising image\" class=\"wp-image-7607\"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->','Services','','inherit','closed','closed','','7428-revision-v1','','','2020-08-06 02:14:58','2020-08-06 02:14:58','',7428,'https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/7428-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(7649,1,'2020-08-05 04:31:38','2020-08-05 04:31:38','','invitefriends','','inherit','open','closed','','invitefriends','','','2020-08-05 04:31:38','2020-08-05 04:31:38','',7324,'http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/invitefriends.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(7650,1,'2020-08-05 04:33:03','2020-08-05 04:33:03','<!-- wp:atomic-blocks/ab-drop-cap -->\n<div style=\"color:#32373c\" class=\"wp-block-atomic-blocks-ab-drop-cap drop-cap-letter ab-font-size-3 ab-block-drop-cap\"><div class=\"ab-drop-cap-text\"><p>So you\'re tasked with setting up your business Facebook page, and you have no idea what you\'re doing. Or you have a Facebook business page but it\'s not setup optimally. Don\'t fret, this walkthrough is for you! </p></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:atomic-blocks/ab-drop-cap -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7638,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/creataccFB-1024x460.png\" alt=\"business manager img\" class=\"wp-image-7638\"/><figcaption>First you\'re going to go to Facebook Business Manager and create an account. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7640,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/createpageFBBusiness-1024x447.png\" alt=\"create page Facebook business\" class=\"wp-image-7640\"/><figcaption>Next, you\'re going to \"Add\"a page from your Facebook console. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7637,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/choosetemplateFB-1024x473.png\" alt=\"Choose Facebook page template\" class=\"wp-image-7637\"/><figcaption>On the left menu, select templates and tabs. Choose the template that is most applicable to your business. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7641,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pageuserFB-1024x469.png\" alt=\"Facebook business page user\" class=\"wp-image-7641\"/><figcaption>Create your username/ Facebook handle. Try and match the page name, and if it\'s not available try adding your country extension on the end. In my case its AU</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7648,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/getstartedfb-1024x433.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7648\"/><figcaption>Click on the get started button and enter business details. This one is pretty self explanatory. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7639,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/createbuttonFB-1024x448.png\" alt=\"CTA button Facebook business\" class=\"wp-image-7639\"/><figcaption>Click \"add button\" to create a call to action offer. This can be a free consult, a quote, or a discount. Pages with CTA\'s are more likely to get enquiries than those without. Also at this stage you should set your cover image. I didn\'t want a cheesy stock photo so I took a screenshot of my homepage. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7644,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/visitor-postsfb-1024x470.png\" alt=\"Visitor post settings Facebook\" class=\"wp-image-7644\"/><figcaption>Under your settings tab, go to visitor posts. I suggest disabling anyone from being able to post to the page. In the years I\'ve managed social accounts, I have seen competitors and even strangers post irrelevant content such as things promoting their business and so on. Some people can be downright nasty.  This is the kind of thing that will keep you up at night and trust me you don\'t want this. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7642,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/profanityFB-1024x449.png\" alt=\"profanity Facebook filkter\" class=\"wp-image-7642\"/><figcaption>The other setting that is a must is the profanity filter. I set mine set as strong. We all know there are crazies on the internet, and the last thing you want is your brand being tarnished by hateful or abusive language. Do yourself a favour and turn it on. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":7649,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/invitefriends-1024x453.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-7649\"/><figcaption>Don\'t forget to invite your friends to like your page. Facebook will auto populate your friends list, and you can also add anyone by inviting them on email. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Step by step guide to setting up your Facebook business page','','inherit','closed','closed','','7324-revision-v1','','','2020-08-05 04:33:03','2020-08-05 04:33:03',''