is an example of a WordPress post, you could edit this to put information about yourself so readers know where you are coming from. You can create as many posts as you like in order to share with them what is on your mind.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Landing Page','','publish','closed','closed','','landing-page','','','2020-08-22 22:55:11','2020-08-22 22:55:11','',0,'http://alphaomegadigital.com.au/landing-page/',0,'page','',0),(7847,1,'2020-09-11 23:32:40','2020-09-11 23:32:40','<!-- wp:video {\"id\":7307} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video autoplay controls loop src=\"https://alphaomegadigital.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/Social-Media-1360-1.mp4\"></video><figcaption>Create awesome content for more likes, followers and subscribers. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:video -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">When you visit a website that just has a basic service offering and a phone number what\'s your honest first impression? Do they seem trustworthy to you? Or at the very least, does anything on that site motivate you to take action in any way? The answer is most likely no. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Let me paint you a picture. Your cupboard falls off its hinge. You bought a new joiner and it kept coming out. You\'ve tried to fix it to no avail. So you google how to fix a cupboard join, and you find a helpful blog post from a local carpenter on how to fix the exact issue you\'re having. Except you\'re not a carpenter and your cupboard is still broken. Who are you going to call to fix it? The local carpenter with the helpful blog post who has gone out of his way to help you for free, or another carpenter who\'s website sits contentless? Who has built more trust and authority with you, the business with valuable content or the one with nothing? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote {\"className\":\"is-style-large\"} -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-style-large\"><p>The best way to build authority is to create high quality, educational content and continuing to do it over time. \"</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">This is where the saying content is king comes from. Content is the defining difference between action and hesitation, or more bluntly between gaining and losing a sale. I think a lot of businesses have shied away from content marketing, especially those in the service industry because they have the misperception they are giving away their trade secrets for free, particularly to their competitors. In fact, the inverse is true. You are providing examples of why you are worth a potential customers time and how you can provide value to them. You are redeeming yourself amongst a sea of very stiff competition, and setting a great first impression. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Which is why you should offer the best possible content, for free. Good content is relevant to your audience, helpful to solve their problems and well researched. It is detailed enough to truly provide value, and doesn\'t gloss over key bits of information that a reader would need to follow your advice. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">You\'ll know you\'re crushing your content marketing goals when you are getting an increase in engagement on social, and increase in traffic to your website and an increase in people contacting you wanting to work together. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">A rundown of the content services provided are: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"clas